cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

The paper deals with person re-identification, which is a computer vision task, and extensively evaluates the design choices for a deep architecture for this task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the training strategy for the deep architecture, which falls under the scope of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of auxiliary information, such as part detections and attribute predictions, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed method compared to the state of the art, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
